Because of the global inadequacy of PPE, WHO recommends reducing the need for PPE with the use of removable medical equipment, introducing barriers such as window openings, and restricting direct access to the room of a COVID-19 patient to the use of PPE only when specifically required, maintaining a single respirator without compromising the time spent caring for multiple patients, coordinating monitoring and processing of PPE and preventing the use of masks for those who do not show symptoms.
